final_guess:
The Tree of Life (from evolutionary biology)

This is my best guess given the contradictory information. The Tree of Life is:
- Physical in the sense that it represents real organisms
- A "tree" but not in the literal botanical sense
- Not found in any specific climate region
- Doesn't exist in the present day in its complete form (as it's constantly evolving)
- Could be considered "maybe extinct" as many branches have gone extinct
- Not mythological or fictional (despite sharing a name with mythological concepts)
- Not from any specific time period (spans all of evolutionary history)
- Not associated with just one geological era

I recognize this may not be correct, as the information suggests a physical botanical tree, but the timeline contradictions make a literal tree difficult to identify.
